answers.feedback_html: Prokaryotes also come under the domain Archaea.
Prokaryotes do not come under the domain Eukarya.
Both Archaea and Bacteria contains prokaryotes.
Bacteria contain prokaryotes. The prokaryotes cannot classify under the eukarya domain since they are enucleated.
